emotes.msg: Diyas stares into the fragment of crystal for a moment, and he spends a long time seeming to sort through everything he's learning.

Ah, so Felizio sent you to get something translated. I don't trust that one myself, but the invasion of Gharu'n by the blue-skinned dogs was a fresh wound in my heart when I first came here. Still, he works for the Arcanum, and on this world, Isparian differences are best put aside...

This is simply fascinating. Not only are these Apostate Virindi trying to construct their own New Singularity, but they are experimenting in strange and unpredictable elements, like this Aetherium ore. Well, I could go on all day about what's in this note, but maybe you should get it to Felizio as soon as you can.
Isn't it lovely? I do so like the Virindi countenance.
No, no -- you keep that! It's a work of art!
No, no thank you. I don't like the feel of this one.
Diyas al-Yat shivers.
You might try that ... Virindi ... in Yanshi.
Ugh. I don't want that!
Ugh. I don't want that!
No, no thank you. I don't like the feel of this one. And Leopold won't take it either.
Diyas al-Yat shivers.
You might try that ... Virindi ... in Yanshi.
Ugh. I don't want that!
Interesting. I've never seen a Virindi crystal quite like this.
As Diyas gazes into the Message Shard a horrified look washes over his face.
The message encoded within is quite disturbing. I have translated it as best I could, but much of the message I was unable to comprehend.
Interesting...very interesting.
Diyas grasps the Shard tightly. Suddenly he shrieks in pain and drops the Message Shard to the ground.

Did I say interesting? I meant disturbing. Disturbing and painful! It was almost as if I could feel the emotions of whatever twisted creature compiled this shard. Take this, it was the best I was able to do.
You need something translated? Let's see what we have here...
Diyas stares into the crystal for a moment. He looks puzzled as he hands a note to you.
A strange piece of writing, but little surprises me with the Virindi these days.
Another Virindi crystal? Fantastic!
Those Virindi with their tests and their experiments. Why can't we all just get along?
I never tire of translating the soapbox ramblings of the arrogant Virindi.
Diyas looks into the Fractured Message Shard. He quickly writes on a parchment and places it into your pack.
Surprise, surprise. Another Virindi with a serious superiority complex.
I heard that Aruq sent you off to that new fortress in the Direlands. Is this the shard you found there? Fascinating... Let me have a look...
Diyas stares into the fragment of crystal for a moment, and his eyes widen with horror.
The Virindi rebels are gathering their allies again! They seek to step into the gap left by T'thuun's defeat! Quick, take this translation to Aruq, he will make sure the proper people are notified.
Well, this is disturbing...
These Tanada from the House of Water seem to have become the pawns of forces greater than themselves. Here, have a look for yourself.
Ah, a message shard from a Virindi Consul found in the southern land bridge? Most intriguing... Let me see if I can translate it for you...
A strange, cold light emanates from the eyes of Diyas al-Yat as he concentrates on the message shard.

I have translated the shard for you. You should bring that translation to Meshenq. He will know what to do with such dire news. Imagine, Nanjou Shou-Jen corrupted by the chaos Virindi! Such an abomination!

Also, Meshenq has told me he gave you a medallion he took from the Tanada who attacked him. The medallion is attuned to the corrupted spirits of the House of Water Tanada. If you give it to me, I can channel its magic to make it useful to you, but I am afraid it will lose the property that grants you access to the House of Water. Not that you need to go to that foul place any more...

Yes, as I may have mentioned, this medallion is attuned to the corrupted life-force of the Nanjou Shou-Jen who have given themselves to the dominion of the chaotic Virindi... Truly tragic. I can channel the magic in this medallion to be useful to you, but it will no longer grant you access to the House of Water. I can't imagine why you'd want to go back in there, though.
If you don't find this channeled medallion useful, you can just give it to me and I'll compensate you with general training.
Ah, you don't find this useful? A pity. The patterns are so mesmerizing...
Fascinating...
It seems this is some sort of continuation of other experiments I've translated shards for. It seems they are trying to create some sort of penultimate creature, or something along those lines.
Fascinating...
Diyas al-Yat shudders.

This seems to be the research notes on the creation of a "Prodigal Human". It seems Aerbax was trying to create another Martine, but one with more potential, and bound directly to a shard of his own essence! Is this what his recent creations all are? Shards of his essence, given form?
Here, see for yourself.
Excellent! Allow me to translate this for you. Very strange ... I wonder what the Virindi are up to?
Very curious indeed! Those Virindi must be up to something!
Hey, money, I appreciate it. Between my scholarly work and my poetry, I don't make a lot of money. Oh, you didn't know I was a poet? Here's my latest poem, I hope you like it.
Excellent! Allow me to translate this for you. Very strange ... I wonder what the Virindi are up to?
I can't make any sense of this. From what I understand there is a translator at Hebian-to that specializes in this language ... Or was it Cragstone?
This is a new one ... they have some sort of emissary in southern Osteth now?
What's this? What kind of fiendish experiments are they carrying out? And why does this all seem so familiar?
What's this? What kind of fiendish experiments are they carrying out? And why does this all seem so familiar?
What's this, then? This writing ... I ... what's happening?
Diyas al-Yat shivers as he turns, and his eyes glow for just an instant with a purplish light.
What ... happened?
What's this, then? This writing ... I ... what's happening?

What ... happened?
What's this, then? This writing ... I ... what's happening?

What ... happened?
This seems to be a rather lengthy text describing the Virindi. I would really like to have met the writer.
The Quiddity has never spoken so plainly before. Their will is certain. The time to act is now.
This really provides some insight into the inner workings of the impure Virindi. It is such a pity to see broken dolls where there was once such purity. Pity.
This piece of writing is quite interesting ... The renegade Virindi have become much more ambitious and more skilled!
This piece of writing is quite interesting ... The renegade Virindi have become much more ambitious and more skilled!
This piece of writing is quite interesting ... The renegade Virindi have become much more ambitious and more skilled!
Aha! Well, that explains Ecorto over there ...
Aha! Well, that explains Ecorto over there ...
Aha! Well, this explains Ecorto over there ...
I caution you against further pursuit of this entity.
There is sincerity in the writings here. A warped mind that believes it is still pure.
A look into madness. A frightening exposition of a fall further than any before.
A creation gone awry, how the master yearns to re-collect his child.
As the shroud is pulled aside light begins to filter in the darkness.
Greatest success or greatest failure, this tale seems yet untold.
This should never have passed through my hands! Take it from me now before I feel the profanity creep beneath my flesh.
Devices by which to view the world. Increasingly interesting.
Reclamation by the collective ... Isn't that always their way?
It appears the location you found this was to be invaded by the Quiddity.
These are simple orders that were given by a member of a directive -- nothing that important to see here. You might better spend your time writing your own information in books.
Oh, yes, very nice! Leopold gave me some repaired masks -- I will trade you one of those for this broken mask.
Oh, yes, very nice! Leopold gave me some repaired masks -- I will trade you one of those for this broken mask.
Oh, yes, very nice! Leopold gave me some repaired masks -- I will trade you one of those for this broken mask.
Your continued trafficking with forces beyond your ken could earn you a hearty bit of trouble. I've translated this for you, but would rather see you destroy it, than keep it.
A strange, cold light emanates from the eyes of Diyas al-Yat as he concentrates on the message shard.
You say you found this in a dream realm? Inside of a Quiddity seed? That sounds so strangely familiar, even though I am sure I never heard that term before...
A fascinating message. With your permission, I have made a copy of this myself, for my own... illumination.
Most fascinating. There is a resonance to this message shard that you do not see in those that come from most Virindi... A sympathetic resonance that is almost human...

This shard came from Aerbax, did it not? Forgive me, I should not ask such questions. I remember what happened the last time I delved too deeply into the affairs of that one. Here is your translation.
Most fascinating. There is a resonance to this message shard that you do not see in those that come from most Virindi... A sympathetic resonance that is almost human...

This shard came from Aerbax, did it not? Forgive me, I should not ask such questions. I remember what happened the last time I delved too deeply into the affairs of that one. Here is your translation.
Hello! I am studying those most enigmatic beings, the Virindi. I think I can translate their language. Do not ask me how I acquired such knowledge.
I have also been in touch with Leopold, in Ayan Baqur, and he has given me some repaired Virindi masks to trade for broken ones.
